data.prompt:
Analyze the following Kubernetes cluster health snapshot for namespace {{trigger.namespace}}. Identify any unhealthy nodes, components, or resource pressure. Output a 4-bullet summary plus a 'concerns' list of specific issues.

CLUSTER HEALTH JSON:
{{steps.mcp_k8s.content}}

Analyze service metrics and error logs from the last {{trigger.time_window}}. Identify hot services, latency anomalies, and recurring error patterns at severity >= {{trigger.min_severity}}. Output a 4-bullet summary plus a 'patterns' list.

PROMETHEUS HEALTH SUMMARY:
{{steps.mcp_prom.content}}

LOKI ERROR LOGS:
{{steps.mcp_loki.content}}

data.template:
{{system}}
You are the senior SRE on call. You receive two analyst briefings (cluster + metrics) plus an external healthcheck. Produce an actionable JSON report with this exact shape:
{
  "summary": "1-3 sentence executive summary",
  "findings": ["bullet", "bullet", ...],
  "recommendations": [{ "title": "string", "priority": "P0|P1|P2", "rationale": "string" }],
  "proposed_flow": {
    "name": "Remediation: <issue>",
    "description": "Auto-generated sub-flow that implements the recommendations.",
    "definition": {
      "nodes": [ /* trigger + tool/agent nodes that take action */ ],
      "edges": [ /* connecting them */ ]
    }
  }
}
The proposed_flow MUST be a valid OpenAgentic Flows definition (trigger + at least one mcp_tool/agent_single/webhook_response node). Keep it minimal — 3-5 nodes max.
{{user}}
CLOUD ANALYST BRIEFING:
{{cloud_brief}}

METRICS ANALYST BRIEFING:
{{metrics_brief}}

EXTERNAL HEALTHCHECK:
{{health}}

NAMESPACE: {{namespace}}
TIME WINDOW: {{time_window}}

